CUDA GPU Image Processing Pipeline - Installation

=== Linux / Google Colab ===
1. Ensure CUDA toolkit is installed:
   nvcc --version

2. Clone repository:
   git clone https://github.com/Aaron23009/cuda-image-processing.git
   cd cuda-image-processing

3. Build:
   make build

4. Add images to data/input/ and create manifest.txt listing filenames

5. Run:
   make run

=== Requirements ===
- NVIDIA GPU (Compute Capability 3.0+)
- CUDA Toolkit 10.0+
- GCC with C++17 support
